column1: Literacy rate, adult (% ages 15 and older)
SDG 4.6 By 2030, ensure that all youth and a substantial proportion of adults, both men and women,achieve literacy and numeracy
Definition: Percentage of the population ages 15 and older that can, with understanding, both read and write a short simple statement on everyday life.
Source: UNESCO (United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization) Institute for Statistics (2020). Data Centre. http://data.uis.unesco.org. Accessed 21 July 2020.
a: Data refer to the most recent year available during the period specified.
